# Commit Message Template
# Use: git commit (without -m) to open this template

# === FORMAT ===
# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# === TYPES ===
# feat:     New feature
# fix:      Bug fix
# refactor: Code refactoring (no behavior change)
# docs:     Documentation changes
# style:    Code formatting (no logic change)
# test:     Add/update tests
# chore:    Maintenance (deps, build, config)
# perf:     Performance improvements
# ci:       CI/CD changes
#
# === SCOPES (optional) ===
# backend, frontend, api, docs, deploy, db, ui
#
# === RULES ===
# 1. Subject: Max 50 chars, imperative mood ("Add" not "Added")
# 2. Body: Wrap at 72 chars, explain WHAT and WHY
# 3. Footer: Reference issues (e.g., "Closes #123")
#
# === EXAMPLES ===
# feat(backend): add Groq API integration for LLM inference
#
# - Switch from OpenAI to Groq for cost savings
# - Use llama-3.3-70b-versatile model
# - Add error handling for API failures
#
# Closes #45
# ---------------------------
# Remember to delete these comments before committing!
